properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 10 at 10:04AM PST until February 11 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Las Vegas NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph.

* WHERE...Owens Valley, from Independence to the Inyo County line
along Highway 395.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...High profile vehicles, especially along Highway 395
south of Olancha could see dangerous wind gusts making driving
hazardous. Additionally, gusty winds could blow around unsecured
objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages
may result.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST TUESDAY
